# GitHub Linguist Configuration
# This file tells GitHub's Linguist library how to categorize files in the repository

# Mark all documentation files as documentation (not counted in language statistics)
docs/** linguist-documentation
README_MAIN.md linguist-documentation
*.md linguist-documentation

# Mark media files as documentation
screenshots/** linguist-documentation
screenshots_old/** linguist-documentation

# Mark configuration files
*.yaml linguist-documentation
*.json linguist-documentation
*.xml linguist-documentation

# Ensure core source code is properly detected
# JavaScript/Node.js files are the primary language
*.js linguist-language=JavaScript

# Mark tour_offline directory as documentation/generated
tour_offline/** linguist-documentation

# Vendored dependencies (if tracked)
node_modules/** linguist-vendored
package-lock.json linguist-generated

# Make sure these are recognized as code, not documentation
src/** linguist-detectable
index.js linguist-detectable
